scopeContent.description:
1) 'Photograph of Miss Sydney Fairbrother, cabinet size, No 41019-2, full length sitting on ground in Japanese dress, full face'. 3cm x 2cm.

2) 'Photograph of Miss Sydney Fairbrother, cabinet size, No 41019-3, full length, standing nearly full face, coming down steps in Japanese dress, holding open fan in right hand'. 3cm x 2cm.

3) 'Photograph of Miss Sydney Fairbrother, cabinet size, No 41019-4, full length, standing, figure turned sideways, looking round ¾ with head down & arms folded'. 3cm x 2cm.

4) 'Photograph of 'The Darling of the Gods', whole plate size, No 41017-5. Group of three, in Japanese dress, woman kneeling on ground, & man standing over her, raising sword in both hands. A young man with sword in right hand standing at right of picture'. 3cm x 4cm.

5) 'Photograph of 'The Darling of the Gods', whole plate size, No 41017-6. Group of three in Japanese dress, old man with hat on holding curtain, young man standing facing him with both hands folded over two swords. Woman with figure bent standing behind young man'. 3cm x 4cm.

6) 'Photograph of 'The Darling of the Gods', whole plate size, No 41017-7. Group of four in Japanese dress, man & woman kneeling on cushions on ground in centre. A man & woman standing one each side of them, each holding small low stool'. 3cm x 4cm.

7) 'Photograph of 'The Darling of the Gods', cabinet size, No 41017-8. Group of two, in Japanese dress, one woman kneeling on ground bending body very low, with face to ground, another woman standing, figure bent holding bunch of flowers'. 3cm x 2cm.

8) 'Photograph of 'The Darling of the Gods', cabinet size, No 41017-9. Group of two, in Japanese dress, two women seated on steps, the lower one smoking long pipe held to small bowl, the top one holding the small case supporting the bowl'. 3cm x 2cm.

9) 'Photograph of 'The Darling of the Gods', cabinet size, No 41017-10. Group of two women in Japanese dress, one sitting full face, on bottom step smoking straight pipe, another woman sitting on top step pointing with right hand'. 3cm x 2cm.

10) 'Photograph of 'The Darling of the Gods', cabinet size, No 41017-11. Group of two, in Japanese dress, woman sitting on ground looking up at man, bending over her holding lantern in left hand'. 3cm x 2cm.

11) 'Photograph of 'The Darling of the Gods', cabinet size, No 41017-13. Group of two, woman kneeling on ground holding man in her arms, lying full length on ground'. 3cm x 2cm.

12) 'Photograph of 'The Darling of the Gods', cabinet size, No 41017-14. Group of two in Japanese dress, woman standing on steps playing musical instrument a man lying full length at her feet'. 3cm x 2cm.

13) 'Photograph of 'The Darling of the Gods', cabinet size, No 41017-15. Group of two in Japanese dress, a man & woman kneeling on cushion on ground, she holding book, both looking down at it, he with his arms right round her'. 3cm x 2cm.

14) 'Photograph of 'The Darling of the Gods', cabinet size, No 41017-16, group of two in Japanese dress, a man & woman sitting on cushions on ground, he holding long pipe to lips, she looking up at him'. 3cm x 2cm.

15) 'Photograph of 'The Darling of the Gods', cabinet size, No 41017-18. Group of two, in Japanese dress, man & woman sitting on cushions on ground, she feeding him with chop sticks'. 3cm x 2cm.

16) 'Photograph of 'The Darling of the Gods', cabinet size, No 41017-17. Group of two in Japanese dress, man & woman standing together, he holding sword in right hand, his left hand round her shoulder'. 3cm x 2cm.

scopeContent.description:
1) 'Photograph of Miss Ellaline Terriss & Mr Seymour Hicks, cabinet size, No 41334-4. Group of two, heads only looking through curtain, Miss Terriss smiling, Mr Hicks as 'Pierrot' with tongue out'.

2) 'Photograph of Miss Ellaline Terriss & Mr Seymour Hicks, cabinet size, No 41334-5. Group of two, Miss Terriss on balcony looking down at Mr Hicks holding out bunch of cherries to him. Mr Hicks standing below her, looking up with hands open dressed as 'Pierrot''.

3) 'Photograph of Miss Ellaline Terriss & Mr Seymour Hicks, cabinet size, No 41334-6. Group of two, Miss Terriss standing, full face, on balcony, holding cherry in right hand near Mr Hicks' mouth. He standing playing mandolin with his tongue out'.

4) 'Photograph of Miss Ellaline Terriss & Mr Seymour Hicks, cabinet size, No 41334-7. Group of two, Miss Terriss ¾ face, standing on balcony holding cherries in hands. Mr Hicks standing beneath her playing mandolin, his mouth wide open'.

5) 'Photograph of Miss Ellaline Terriss & Mr Seymour Hicks, cabinet size, No 41334-8. Group of two, Miss Terriss standing, full face, with large bonnet on, holding up dress with left hand & Mr Hicks' arm with right hand. Mr Hicks standing, ¾ face, with moustache on & tall hat, holding cane in left hand'.

6) 'Photograph of Miss Ellaline Terriss, cabinet size, No 41132-14, ¾ length, full face, with cap on sitting on side of well, holding the rope with left hand, right hand on knee'.

9) 'Photograph of Miss Ellaline Terriss, cabinet size, No 41132-17, ¾ length, full face, kneeling on balcony leaning against tree, holding the trunk with left hand & pulling down branches with right hand'.

10) 'Photograph of Miss Ellaline Terriss, cabinet size, No 41132-18, ¾ length, profile, holding up bird cage in both hands looking at it'.
